descript.abstract: Table StreetAddress publishes an entry for each navigable link. One navigable link can have multiple Street Address entries when: * Multiple names exist for the Link * Multiple address ranges exist for the Link. A Street Address therefore represents a named and addressed Link. Note: Unnamed navigable links do not have an entry in the StreetAddress table. Unnamed Links are available in the Link table for geocoding purposes (e.g. reverse geocoding).
descript.purpose: Road network navigation and routing, geocoding, location-based services, and base mapping applications.

attracc.attraccr: HERE advanced map-building capabilities, local field staff and a fleet of LIDAR equipped TRUE vehicles capture the world down to centimeter level precision to build a virtual 3D model of the real world. In addition, internal test applications are regularly run on attributes to assist in verification and correction.

dataqual.logic: HERE publishes Technical Notification Memorandums (TNM) for customers on a quarterly and weekly basis via HERE TNM Web Portal. These TNMs include information pertaining to product updates, format changes, new attributes, detailed attribute specifications and representations, and new country coverage announcements. If HERE plans to add, remove, or change an attribute or product Layer, an announcement is made to customers a minimum of 6 months in advance. This allows customers to prepare and make necessary modifications to their applications before a new attribute is released in the product.
dataqual.complete: HERE includes 4 levels of street map coverage: Prime, Complete, Network, and City-to-City. Prime is HERE's highest level of coverage. This coverage level has the most detail and enables door-to-door routing functionality. Complete is a level of coverage, which is source dependent. It is the coverage level used for links that are not field verified and are flagged with the In-Process Data attribute = Y. Network coverage includes the main highway network and all the necessary attributes required to allow routing from city to city. Network links are coded with Detailed City Inclusion attribute = N and In-Process Data attribute = N. For Network links, the Full Geometry flag may be set to either yes or no depending on the presence or lack of surrounding In-Process Data Coverage. The City-to-City specification enables HERE to maintain minimum coverage in areas prior to completing Prime, Network, or In- Process areas. Examples include: major roads only in a country where there is no existing coverage, major roads to a city in a country where there is currently no other existing coverage, or major roads between existing DC/Prime, IT/Network, or In-Process areas. In many countries, HERE has used a commercial source to add local roads to the Inter-Town network. The inclusion of this geometry allows improved map display and guidance. This coverage level is called Full Coverage in the U.S. and Road Network Coverage in Europe. The Connector Specification enables HERE to maintain minimum coverage in areas prior to completing (full) Prime, Network/Inter Town (IT), or In-Process areas. For defining a hierarchical network used to determine a logical and efficient route for a traveler, each map street segment is tagged with a 5 level Functional Class (FC) attribute explained as follows. FC 1: Very long distance routes between major cities - The "highest level" network comprises the FC 1 arterials, which are primarily controlled access highways designed for very-long-distance travel linking major metropolitan areas and cities, FC 2: Primary routes between major and smaller cities and through metro areas, FC 3: Major routes between minor cities or towns, and through city districts, FC 4: Routes connecting minor towns or villages and collecting the local traffic in the city districts, and FC 5: Roads that are not efficient through routes - The "lowest level" and final category is FC 5, which comprises roads not considered to be arterials or transportation corridors.

procstep.procdesc: HERE File Geodatabase Plus is assembled from the following data sources: HERE North America FGDB, HERE Traffic Patterns, HERE Postal Code Boundaries, and HERE enhanced network routing and geocoding data entities and locators.

Using proprietary tools and processes, HERE collects road geometry and approximately 400 road attributes. Proprietary software is used to add navigable information, addresses, and points of interest. TRUE vehicles and photos capture overhead signage to ensure that the data accurately reflects the real world.

HERE relies on local source data and input from map users to generate constant daily map updates, such as real time traffic, turn by turn directions, public transportation routes and information about local business and attractions.
HERE allows end users to update map content through the HERE Map Creator program, which provides online cartographic and data editing capabilities (https://mapcreator.here.com).

enttyp.enttypd: Table StreetAddress publishes an entry for each navigable link. One navigable link can have multiple Street Address entries when: * Multiple names exist for the Link * Multiple address ranges exist for the Link. A Street Address therefore represents a named and addressed Link. Note: Unnamed navigable links do not have an entry in the StreetAddress table. Unnamed Links are available in the Link table for geocoding purposes (e.g. reverse geocoding).

attr.attrdef: Object ID - ESRI unique ID.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all OBJECTID values

attr.attrdef: Street Address ID - Unique identifier for a named, addressed navigable link.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all STREET_ADDRESS_ID values

attr.attrdef: Link ID - Unique identifier for the Link to which the Street Address relates. Link ID is used to identify each link in the database.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all LINK_ID values

attr.attrdef: ISO Country Code - A three-letter country code as defined by the International Organization for Standardization. The ISO Country Code indicates in which country the feature is located. Different layers describe different features. ISO Country Code attribution is applied to Navigable Links, Administrative Hierarchies, and POIs in various layers.

Language Code - The language associated with the feature name. The Language Code, in conjunction with Prefix, Feature Name, Street Type, and Suffix, can be used in destination selection, route guidance, and map display.
Street Name - The Street Name attribute is the full spelling of the street name including the Street Name Prefix, Street Name Suffix and Street Type.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all STREET_NAME values

attr.attrdef: Base Name - The Base Name part of the Street Name.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all BASE_NAME values

attr.attrdef: Street Type - The full street type of the Street Name (e.g., Avenue del la, Via della or Ave).

attrdomv.udom: The set of all STREET_TYPE values

attr.attrdef: Street Type Full Spelling - Street Type Full Spelling stores the full spelling of the Street Type.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all STREET_TYPE_FULL_SPELLING values

attr.attrdef: Street Type Before - Street Type Before indicates if the Street Type is before or after the Base Name. Street Type Before can be used to determine the placement of the Street Type for usage in destination selection, map display and route guidance.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all STREET_TYPE_BEFORE values

attr.attrdef: Street Type Attached - Street Type Attached indicates whether the Street Type is attached or separated by a space fromthe Base Name. Street Type Attached can be used to determine the location of the Street Type for usage in destination selection, map display and route guidance.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all STREET_TYPE_ATTACHED values

attr.attrdef: Prefix - Prefix is a directional identifier that precedes the Feature Name of a road.
Suffix - Suffix is a directional identifier that follows, but is not included in, the Feature Name of a road.

Route Type - The route type indicates that the road's name is actually a route number and in many countries is displayed in a shield symbol (i.e. Interstate and State routes in the U.S.). Name Route Type can be used for display and map publication to display the appropriate route shield when used in conjunction with the Direction on Sign.

Direction On Sign - The official directional identifiers assigned to highways. Direction on Sign should be used in conjunction with Feature Name, Name on Road Sign, and Name Route Type. For route guidance, US-101 South should be used and not just US-101 when appropriate.

Is Name on Road Signe - Name on Road Sign indicates the name assigned to a road by the official organisation responsible for the existence and maintenance of the road. Name on Road Sign is generally the name posted on the street signs. For destination selection any name may be used. However only names with Name on Road Sign = Y and Exit Number = Y should be used for route guidance. A link may have more than one name with Name on Road Sign = Y. There is no distinction in this case to which name is more important than the other name.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all IS_NAME_ON_ROAD_SIGN values

attr.attrdef: Is Explicatable - Explicatable indicates which names should be used to identify a given road when providing directions. Names with Name on Road Sign = Y or Exit Number = Y are always suitable for explication. Other names on a link may or may not be. The Explicatable flag will show this. Names which are Explicatable = N are included in the database to assist in destination selection but are not recommended for route guidance.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all IS_EXPLICATABLE values

attr.attrdef: Is Junction Name - Junction Name identifies a ramp system that comprises a named Junction between two or more motorways or a named motorway exit/entrance. Junction Name allows for explication of an exit or entry ramp that comprises a named junction without having to use the sign text.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all IS_JUNCTION_NAME values

attr.attrdef: Is Exit Name - Exit Name identifies a name that is an (alpha)numeric exit name. An exit number (Exit Name = Y) as a feature name can be used for destination selection.

Is Stale Name - Stale Name identifies old names that are still in use. Stale Name records are included in the database to assist in destination selection but should never be used during route guidance or map display.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all IS_STALE_NAME values

attr.attrdef: Is Postal Name - Postal Name identifies additional names that are added to a link merely to match a postal service file. They could not be verified on any other sources or by field research. Postal Names are included in the database to assist in destination selection but should never be used during route guidance or map display.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all IS_POSTAL_NAME values

attr.attrdef: Is Vanity Name - Vanity Name identifies an alternative name (specific to a business, settlement, location, etc.) other than the official street name. The Vanity Name may only apply to one building along the street (e.g. IBM Plaza). Vanity Names are included in the database to assist in address identification and may be used for route guidance.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all IS_VANITY_NAME values

attr.attrdef: Is Scenic Name - Scenic Route Name identifies a unique name that represents a Scenic Route. Scenic Route Name can be used for destination selection and map display.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all IS_SCENIC_NAME values

attr.attrdef: Left Start Address - This is the house number on the left side of the the reference end of the Link. The Left Start Address is used in conjunction with related address attributes and the associated name for destination selection and geocoding.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all LEFT_START_ADDRESS values

attr.attrdef: Left End Address - This is the house number on the left side of the non-reference end of the Link. The Left End Address is used in conjunction with related address attributes and the associated name for destination selection and geocoding.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all LEFT_END_ADDRESS values

attr.attrdef: Left Scheme - The numbering scheme for the addresses assigned to the left side of the link. The Left Address Scheme is used in conjunction with related address attributes and the associated name for destination selection and geocoding.

Left Address Format - The format of the addresses on the left side of the link. The Left Address Format is used in conjunction with related address attributes and the associated name for destination selection and geocoding.

Right Start Address - This is the house number on the right side of the the reference end of the Link. The right Start Address is used in conjunction with related address attributes and the associated name for destination selection and geocoding.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all RIGHT_START_ADDRESS values

attr.attrdef: Right End Address - This is the house number on the right side of the non-reference end of the Link. The right End Address is used in conjunction with related address attributes and the associated name for destination selection and geocoding.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all RIGHT_END_ADDRESS values

attr.attrdef: Right Scheme - The numbering scheme for the addresses assigned to the right side of the link. The Right Address Scheme is used in conjunction with related address attributes and the associated name for destination selection and geocoding.

Right Address Format - The format of the addresses on the right side of the link. The Right Address Format is used in conjunction with related address attributes and the associated name for destination selection and geocoding.

Address Type - Address Type identifies the type of the house number range assigned to the link. The Address Type is used in conjunction with related address attributes, and the associated name for destination selection and geocoding.

Road Name ID - The Road Name ID defines a unique identifier for the Street Name to which the Street Address relates. The Road Name ID can be used to associate Transliterations and Phonetic Data to Street Names.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all ROAD_NAME_ID values

attr.attrdef: Subtype - ESRI Geodatabase Subtype.

attrdomv.udom: The set of all SUBTYPE values
